      "message": "Issue #1: Missing Redfish API State Verification After GUI Toggle\n\nLocation: Line 240 in gui/gui_test/security_and_access_menu/test_policies_sub_menu.robot\n\nIssue: Test toggles GUI but doesn\u0027t explicitly verify the Redfish API state changed to False before testing authentication. While Toggle Policy Option And Verify Toast Message verifies GUI state, it doesn\u0027t confirm the backend API property ${resp[\"Oem\"][\"OpenBMC\"][\"AuthMethods\"][\"BasicAuth\"]} actually changed to False.\n\nFix: Add explicit Redfish API verification after GUI toggle:\n# After line 237, add:\n```\n${resp_after}\u003d  Redfish.Get Properties  ${REDFISH_ACCOUNTS_SERVICE_URI}\nShould Be Equal  ${resp_after[\"Oem\"][\"OpenBMC\"][\"AuthMethods\"][\"BasicAuth\"]}  ${False}\n...  msg\u003dBasicAuth API state did not change after GUI toggle\n```\n\nWhy: Ensures GUI changes propagate to backend API, preventing false positives if GUI toggle succeeds but API state doesn\u0027t change",
